history.content:
Hey everyone!

If autonomous lunar rovers, microgravity experiments, high altitude balloons, and designing/launching satellites sound like projects you want to make part of your Berkeley experience, come join us at the Space Technologies at California (STAC) Fall 2021 info sessions!

Info Session Date: Jacobs 310

  • Tuesday, September 7th  8-9pm

STAC is a student space program that strives to push the space industry incrementally further. Our 60+ members come from all majors and backgrounds and collaborate on several innovative research projects throughout the year. Come meet our members, hear about what we're working on, and learn how you can make an impact in the space industry!

p.s. there will be free food :)


We have a very chill application process which will be opening soon and will be due Sunday, 9/12 at 11:59 PM: stac.berkeley.edu/join

Questions?: execs@stac.berkeley.edu
